headline: Apple to update EU browser options, make more apps deletable
summary: STOCKHOLM (Reuters) -Apple will change how users choose browser options in the European Union, add a dedicated section for changing default apps, and make more apps deletable, the company said on Thursday.  The iPhone maker came under pressure from regulators to make changes after the EU's sweeping Digital Markets Act took effect on March 7, forcing it to offer mobile users the ability to select from a list of available web browsers on a "choice screen" the first time they open Safari.  In an update later this year, Apple users will be able to select a default browser directly from the choice screen after going through a mandatory list of options.
